msgid "This page is intended for advanced users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:9
#: dff6bc29fa1e43f395ff88d4ca999295
msgid ""
"When a Qubes OS install is unbootable or booting it is otherwise "
"undesirable, this process allows for the recovery of files stored within the"
" system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:11
#: 1dc95a1648fb49b285c94d426db4c4d7
msgid ""
"These functions are manual and do not require any Qubes specific tools. All "
"steps assume the default Qubes install with the following components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:13
#: b12af31cca7d44b4937ef13c685f0e18
msgid "LUKS encrypted disk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:15
#: 6054fb0207634b53a433c2003b562942
msgid "LVM based VM storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:19
#: 1ad5ad8e4189435e8cf9e42217318571
msgid ""
"Before beginning, if attempting to access one Qubes system from another, it "
"is recommended to pass the entire encrypted Qubes disk to an isolated app "
"qube. This can be done with the command ``qvm-block attach <isolated vm> "
"dom0:<disk>`` in dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:22
#: bc2cf28363b14053a8d9f4307fe786f6
msgid "Decrypting the Disk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:25
#: 765eb2139a55476dbd133ca50b87ad82
msgid "Find the disk to be accessed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:27
#: 8a4747d6a9134ae1b961d88a21ce9a0d
msgid ""
"Open a Linux terminal in either dom0 or the app qube the disk was passed "
"through to and enter ``lsblk``, which will result in an output similar to "
"the following. In this example, the currently booted Qubes system is "
"installed on ``sda`` and the qubes system to be accessed is on "
"``nvme0n1p2``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:59
#: 4f7613384e9a4f05abeba74b30fc74bd
msgid ""
"Decrypt the disk using the command ``cryptsetup luksOpen /dev/<disk>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:64
#: 4bc017a33a2546eabed732f5dae09b8d
msgid "Accessing LVM Logical Volumes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:67
#: 271a81bbbf6f496abcaab9d36ab407c7
msgid ""
"If using an app qube or standard Linux, LVM should automatically discover "
"the Qubes LVM configuration. In this case, continue to step 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:69
#: 256e8ac2cd5440638d1099d4761e9e2d
msgid ""
"Qubes uses the default name ``qubes_dom0`` for it’s LVM VG. This will "
"conflict with the name of the VG of the currently installed system. To read "
"both, you will have to rename the VG. *Note:* If this is not reversed, the "
"Qubes install being accessed will not be bootable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:71
#: f60d13f1bfe4486093fa93183895272e
msgid ""
"Find the UUID of the vg to be accessed using the command ``vgdisplay``. This"
" will be the VG named ``qubes_dom0`` which is not marked active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:73
#: bed93c4621e247139981e1d6097632f2
msgid "The command ``vgrename <UUID> other_install`` will rename the VG."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/mount-from-other-os.rst:77
#: b5efae8215d14735ac6d4705845d8495
msgid "Run the command ``vgscan`` to add any new VGs to the device list."
msgstr ""

